\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The Purpose of Bankruptcy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The fundamental role of bankruptcy law is to facilitate debt collection,
 keeping economic efficiency in consideration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Private Workout or Bankruptcy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Both cases involve exchanging new financial claims for old ones (senior
 debt is replaced with junior debt; junior debt is replaced with stock).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Private workouts are usually better than a bankruptcy, when they work.
 Complex structure and lack of information make them more likely.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Debt financing: chapter 11 allows the firm to ask for more financing, if
 the new debt is first in line (overriding allo ther claims).
 It might be needed to have a high enough value of the firm's assets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bankruptcy advantages:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
New credit availability
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Discontinued accrual of interest (it stops after filing for bankruptcy)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Tax advantages
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Requires only a small portion of creditors to approve
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bankruptcy disadvantages:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A long & expensive process
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Judges approve business decisions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Management distraction (huge number of court appearances)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Hold out
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 by stockholders
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Prepackaged Bankruptcy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One way of reducing the bankruptcy costs is the 
\series bold
prepackaged bankruptcy
\series default
.
 It is an agreement which is made before the legal filing.
 It has some advantages of a formal bankruptcy, but is more efficient.
\end_layout

