\begin_layout Subsection
Absolute Priority Rule
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
According to the APR, the order of preference of the bankruptcy procedure
 is strictly followed, i.e senior claims are 
\series bold
fully
\series default
 satisfied, before junior claims receive 
\series bold
anything
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In practice, violations are common: in most cases equityholders receive
 payout, while creditors do not receive their full payout.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The reasons for that include bargaining.
 Creditors try to avoid litigation expenses, debtors have a 120-day opportunity
 window which is usued by the management (who has equity).
 While judges like c onsensual plans (appeals are less likely).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Reorganization (Chapter 11) - Continued
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Step 1 - Gaining Control
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All pre-petition claims automatically stay.
 First-day motions need permission to enter into contracts and make critical
 payments and DIP financing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

restructuring officer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 may be hired in order for the company to continue to operate with the existing
 management.
 A relief from all pre-petition unpaif interest, principal and lease results
 in a sudden cash flow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Step 2 - Restructuring
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Section 363 Sales - assets can be sold by a judge approval in order to generate
 cash (following an auction procedure to get the highest possible price).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Section 365 Contracs & Leases: modify leases and other contracts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Step 3 - Reorganization
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First, the total enterprise value (TEV) of the core business is determined
 using valuation techniques.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then pre-petition claims are settled using cash, debt or stock.
 Secured (collateralized) creditors are paid at least the value of their
 collateral and cannot be forced to take equity instead - unlike unsecured
 creditors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The Fulcrum Claim
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Two critical issues in Chapter 11 PORs are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The TEV of the business
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How much debt can be reasonably carried
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The TEV is allocated until it is exhausted, starting from the first priority.
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Impaired
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 creditors likely receive most of the equity.
 The equity has an unlimited upside potential (unlike debt), therefore it
 might acquire a position with enormous potential.
\end_layout

